25,-0.00099334,-0.04757370,0.00543425,-0.04715013,0.03078660,0.00217126,-0.07072614,-0.05327855,-0.05326857,0.07126661,-0.03281034,0.04501892,-0.02185184,0.02022768,-0.01608567,-0.00236182,0.01645487,-0.06178797,0.00305096,-0.01369335,0.01006540,0.04015750,-0.02176511,-0.01279983,-0.05287611,-0.05062879,0.04401580,0.05034063,-0.08294334,-0.01456122,-0.01362037,0.03023671,0.00322340,-0.00232057,0.00067723,-0.03808278,0.02686430,-0.00913909,-0.05604113,0.03892659,-0.03602619,-0.01221290]',E'Attaching Rate Limiters to Routes\n\nRate limiters may be attached to routes or route groups using the `throttle` [middleware](/docs/{{version}}/middleware). The throttle middleware accepts the name of the rate limiter you wish to assign to the route:\n\n```php\nRoute::middleware([''throttle:uploads''])->group(function () {\n    Route::post(''/audio'', function () {\n        // ...\n    });\n\n    Route::post(''/video'', function () {\n        // ...\n    });\n});\n```\n\n<a name="throttling-with-redis"></a>','{"source": "laravel", "version": "12", "language": "php", "title": "Routing", "section_title": "routing", "url": "https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/routing.md", "topics": "laravel,php,routing", "categories": "web,php,fullstack,orm"}');
