.02365880,0.08131335,-0.00066408,0.02171619,-0.02106165,0.03852264,-0.03278442,0.01708281,-0.05154720,0.07703952,-0.05178086,0.01855491,-0.01665794,0.00125809,-0.02050614,0.02609332,0.03390076,-0.10284695,-0.01694801,0.01964218,0.01638115,0.03801567,-0.03808809,-0.02976631,-0.06020511,-0.10665096,0.04435082,0.01542975,-0.01965571,-0.02262645,-0.02572722,0.02449901,0.05184038,-0.01214365,0.02217231,-0.03251045,0.01626700,0.02117265,0.07739144,0.06149449,0.01254908,-0.01102332]',E'Single Action Controllers\n\nIf a controller action is particularly complex, you might find it convenient to dedicate an entire controller class to that single action. To accomplish this, you may define a single `__invoke` method within the controller:\n\n```php\n<?php\n\nnamespace App\\Http\\Controllers;\n\nclass ProvisionServer extends Controller\n{\n    /**\n     * Provision a new web server.\n     */\n    public function __invoke()\n    {\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```','{"source": "laravel", "version": "12", "language": "php", "title": "Controllers", "section_title": "controllers", "url": "https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/controllers.md", "topics": "laravel,php,controllers", "categories": "web,php,fullstack,orm"}');
