,0.02839423,0.01945715,0.04363925,-0.00362428,-0.01167597,0.04615472,0.01398243,-0.04338436,-0.02088618,0.07492474,0.00972052,0.01776471,-0.05611189,0.00642976,0.02728790,0.04496003,-0.05869305,-0.12566964,0.07053414,0.05306402,-0.05943000,0.05589495,-0.01334431,0.01429535,0.03567706,-0.07148923,-0.00237991,0.03530612,0.01076826,0.00877314,0.02281267,0.03971849,0.04071761,-0.00608022,0.03108013,0.07189256,0.02834519,0.05080468,0.03941733,0.03534899,-0.01422155,-0.05878475]',E'Saving a Single Model Without Events\n\nSometimes you may wish to "save" a given model without dispatching any events. You may accomplish this using the `saveQuietly` method:\n\n```php\n$user = User::findOrFail(1);\n\n$user->name = ''Victoria Faith'';\n\n$user->saveQuietly();\n```\n\nYou may also "update", "delete", "soft delete", "restore", and "replicate" a given model without dispatching any events:\n\n```php\n$user->deleteQuietly();\n$user->forceDeleteQuietly();\n$user->restoreQuietly();\n```','{"source": "laravel", "version": "12", "language": "php", "title": "Eloquent: Getting Started", "section_title": "eloquent", "url": "https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/eloquent.md", "topics": "laravel,php,eloquent", "categories": "web,php,fullstack,orm"}');
