731,-0.03269378,0.05489565,0.06879884,0.02791482,0.01782015,0.10023496,0.02953051,-0.00916127,-0.03388846,0.08163534,-0.04007953,0.05553959,-0.13487396,-0.00090484,-0.09400216,0.01525007,-0.07238805,-0.08502629,-0.01711114,0.05108931,-0.04034551,0.05415178,-0.05385057,-0.03155842,0.00401072,0.05373695,-0.00875103,-0.00159704,-0.07520930,-0.04117098,0.05858498,0.03352227,0.05879077,-0.03358574,-0.04773040,0.02652962,-0.00178872,0.00581384,0.02256499,0.05095619,-0.03668092,0.00742784]',E'Logging Out\n\nTo manually log users out of your application, you may use the `logout` method provided by the `Auth` facade. This will remove the authentication information from the user''s session so that subsequent requests are not authenticated.\n\nIn addition to calling the `logout` method, it is recommended that you invalidate the user''s session and regenerate their [CSRF token](/docs/{{version}}/csrf). After logging the user out, you would typically redirect the user to the root of your application:\n\n```php\nuse Illuminate\\Http\\Request;\nuse Illuminate\\Http\\RedirectResponse;\nuse Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Auth;\n\n/**\n * Log the user out of the application.\n */\npublic function logout(Request $request): RedirectResponse\n{\n    Auth::logout();\n\n    $request->session()->invalidate();\n\n    $request->session()->regenerateToken();\n\n    return redirect(''/'');\n}\n```\n\n<a name="invalidating-sessions-on-other-devices"></a>','{"source": "laravel", "version": "12", "language": "php", "title": "Authentication", "section_title": "authentication", "url": "https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/authentication.md", "topics": "laravel,php,authentication", "categories": "web,php,fullstack,orm"}');
