,0.03918618,0.00525760,0.05570342,-0.01220420,-0.00511385,-0.01956216,0.00209475,-0.00997996,-0.01762192,0.00025134,-0.00615982,0.00692423,0.01911342,-0.04870072,0.03578870,-0.00887035,-0.04855743,-0.08316119,0.02727227,-0.00425214,-0.00858080,0.03320444,-0.05259297,-0.04052744,-0.04334665,-0.03127655,0.05745035,-0.01175198,-0.03071720,-0.08674889,-0.01274732,0.04964166,0.04404631,-0.01198947,0.02430548,0.00224713,0.01216227,0.01982165,-0.02633674,0.09469835,0.01211455,-0.02409060]',E'Running Migrations\n\nTo run all of your outstanding migrations, execute the `migrate` Artisan command:\n\n```shell\nphp artisan migrate\n```\n\nIf you would like to see which migrations have already run and which are still pending, you may use the `migrate:status` Artisan command:\n\n```shell\nphp artisan migrate:status\n```\n\nIf you provide the `--step` option to the `migrate` command, the command will run each migration as its own batch, allowing you to roll back individual migrations later using the `migrate:rollback` command:\n\n```shell\nphp artisan migrate --step\n```\n\nIf you would like to see the SQL statements that will be executed by the migrations without actually running them, you may provide the `--pretend` flag to the `migrate` command:\n\n```shell\nphp artisan migrate --pretend\n```\n\n<a name="isolating-migration-execution"></a>','{"source": "laravel", "version": "12", "language": "php", "title": "Database: Migrations", "section_title": "migrations", "url": "https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/migrations.md", "topics": "laravel,php,migrations", "categories": "web,php,fullstack,orm"}');
